The paper focuses on the cyber-physical security and safety of autonomous connected vehicles, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper also proposes an optimal safe controller for ACVs, which involves optimization and control theory, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes data injection attack detection approaches, which involve machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories.
